-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Comgas, Kroton, Transmissao Paulista
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2012-05-29T21:03:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/brazilian-stock-movers-comgas-kroton-transmissao-paulista.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close. Preferred shares
are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index fell 1 percent to 54,633.06.  Kroton Educacional SA (KROT11 BS),  Brazil ’s second-biggest
education company, rose 4.9 percent to 28.75 reais, the most
since Aug. 30. The company said its Editora e Distribuidora
Educacional SA unit acquired college operator Grupo Uniasselvi
for 510 million reais ($256 million).  Cia de Gas de Sao Paulo  (CGAS3 BS) advanced 1.1 percent to
38 reais.  Cosan SA Industria e Comercio  said in a regulatory
filing it completed an agreement to buy BG Group Plc’s 60.1
percent stake in Comgas, as the distributor of natural gas
throughout the state of Sao Paulo is known, for 3.4 billion
reais. The deal was announced earlier this month. Cosan lost 0.6
percent to 29.43 reais.  Cia de Transmissao de Energia Eletrica Paulista  (TRPL4 BS)
fell 2.5 percent to 59.80 reais, the lowest in two months, after
the company’s board approved the acquisition of Evrecy
Participacoes Ltda. from EDP  Energias do Brasil  SA for 58.43
million reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denyse Godoy in  Sao Paulo  at 
